        public ImmutableMapImpl checkpoint()
        Specified by:
        checkpoint in interface ImmutableMap
        Returns:
        a new instance of ImmutableMap, which inherits all values from this ImmutableMap Any call of ImmutableMap.putValue(String, Object) is remembered in local Map of parameters. At the end of process the ImmutableMap.getModifiedValues() can be used to return all the parameters which were changed after local ImmutableMap was created
